<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Draya Michele has amassed quite the following since first appearing on Basketball Wives LA back in 2011. </p>

<p>And the reality TV personality is staying busy during the COVID-19 pandemic, churning out content for her 8.1 million Instagram followers.</p>

<p>She served '90s vibes Monday in a yellow halter top and baggy jeans, as a friend photographed her for some Instagram shots in the Los Feliz neighborhood of Los Angeles.</p>

<p>'90s vibes: Draya Michele served '90s vibes Monday in a yellow halter top and baggy jeans, as a friend photographed her for some Instagram shots in the Los Feliz neighborhood of Los Angeles</p>

<p>The 35-year-old teased her taut midriff in the crop top, while showing some hip in the jeans, which were open on the sides and laced up with thin chains.</p>

<p>She finished the ensemble with a pair of gold hoop earrings, matching bangles and blue and purple Nikes with yellow laces, matching her top.</p>

<p>Draya also matched the top with a yellow Chanel handbag, which she showed off in the Instagram shot, writing: 'I be on my grind daily.'  </p>

<p>She previously took to her Instagram Story with a selfie in the look, as she sat on her porch, writing: 'Sitting outside of my crib in yesterday's clothes, stalking packages, and supervising these delivery men.'</p>

<p>Peek-a-boo: The 35-year-old teased her taut midriff in the crop top, while showing some hip in the jeans, which were open on the sides and laced up with thin chains</p>

<p>Accessorizing: She finished the ensemble with a pair of gold hoop earrings, matching bangles and blue and purple Nikes with yellow laces, matching her top</p>

<p>Strike a pose: Draya also matched the top with a yellow Chanel handbag, which she showed off in the Instagram shot, writing: 'I be on my grind daily'</p>

<p>Special delivery: She previously took to her Instagram Story with a selfie in the look, as she sat on her porch, waiting for a package</p>

<p>The Beige &amp; Coco founder has recently landed her own docu-series about her life, which will air on the subscription streaming platform Zeus this fall.</p>

<p>Entitled Doses of Draya, the 10-episode series follows her social life, as she keeps busy building her businesses.</p>

<p>She said in a statement, via Variety: 'I’ve been on a pretty incredible journey over the past decade, and I’m grateful to my fans who have been with me through the ups and downs.</p>

<p>'As a woman of color, I couldn’t be more excited to be working with Zeus, a Black-owned streaming service, to share my story, and to let people into my daily life in a way I never really have before.'</p>

<p>Draya's new show marks her return to reality television, after starring in Basketball Wives LA from 2011 to 2015.</p>

<p>Return to reality: The Beige &amp; Coco founder has recently landed her own docu-series about her life, which will air on the subscription streaming platform Zeus this fall (pictured in November, 2019)</p>
